subSubSection.paragraph:
Walking legs (Figs 2
e-f
) relatively short, merus flattened, ovate from above, 1.4 to 1.5 times longer than wide, surface with scattered, transversal ridges and scattered setae. Carpus and propodus elongate, of similar length, with scattered simple setae, propodus spineless except for terminal triplet. Dactylus elongate, terminating in curved, bifurcate claws, the upper one being smaller, inner margin with two or sometimes three smaller spines.
